name: Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s) * Product_{p prime} (1 + 1/p^(2*s) + 1/p^(3*s)).
comment: First differs from A095691, A365552 and A368105 at n = 32.
The number of divisors of n that are both biquadratefree (A046100) and powerful (A001694). - _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 22 2025
link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: Multiplicative with a(p^e) = e if e < 4 and 3 otherwise. - _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 22 2025
mathematica: f[p_, e_] := If[e < 4, e, 3]; a[1] = 1; a[n_] := Times @@ f @@@ FactorInteger[n]; Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 22 2025 *)
author: _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Apr 22 2025

Vaclav Kotesovec, Graph - the asymptotic ratio (10000 terms)
formula: Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ f(1) * n * (log(n) + 2*gamma - 1 + f'(1)/f(1)), where
and gamma is the Euler-Mascheroni constant A001620.
Multiplicative with a(p^e) = 2 if e <= 2 and 3 otherwise. - _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 22 2025
mathematica: f[p_, e_] := If[e < 3, 2, 3]; a[1] = 1; a[n_] := Times @@ f @@@ FactorInteger[n]; Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 22 2025 *)
